English Premier League (1992/93 - 2021/22) Analysis

Kevin Bradwick

2022-12-26

Overview

This analysis looks at data from the English Premier Leage from 1992/92 to 2021/22 seasons in order to explore the correlation between transfer spending and success on the pitch. The data was scraped from Transfermarkt and can be downloaded from this Github repo.

Permier League Winners

First, let’s take a look at all the title winning clubs and how many times they won it.

Manchester United mark their historic dominance with a total of 13 Premier League title wins in 30 seasons. We can take a look at how much each club spent on average and as a total for their title wins.

Expenditure for each title win
Club names Total Expenditure (M) EUR Average per title (M) EUR
